summary: This document contains corporate resolutions authorizing Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas to manage accounts for a corporation. It outlines the powers granted to authorized signers and the responsibilities of the bank in relation to these accounts. The document emphasizes the authority of the signers and the indemnification of the bank.
keyFacts: The document certifies corporate resolutions for account management with Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas.
It specifies the powers granted to authorized signers for managing the corporation's accounts.
The bank is indemnified against claims arising from actions taken by the authorized signers.
No other entity has an interest in the accounts opened in the name of the corporation.
The document confirms that previous authorities granted to any signer not named are revoked.
